<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Loses Opener in HK Int'l Basketball Tournament </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 1 (Xinhua) -- China lost to Singapore's Sin Kee
Tycoon in the extra-time of their first match at the Henderson Cup
Basketball Championship for Celebration of Hong Kong's
Reunification with China here on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
In the other match of the day, Hong Kong's Winling beat Fukien
89-82 after leading 49-43 at half-time.
</P>
<P>
China led the first half 40-33, but the score was leveled three
times in the second half before the two sides tied at 74-74 after
the 40-minute regular play.
</P>
<P>
China sprang to an initial lead at 81-74, but the Singapore
side made it even at 81-81 when there was only a bit more than one
minute left for the match.
</P>
<P>
Poor form of some of the Chinese players cost them any chance
in the dying minute when the Singapore team scored two more points
in a row to seal their victory.
</P>
<P>
On Monday, Fukien takes on Seapower while Winling meets Sin Kee
Tycoon.
</P>
<P>
The five teams play a single round-robin preliminary round from
Sunday through Thursday. The top four teams enter the semi-finals
on Friday and the Championship final is slated for Saturday.
</P>
</TEXT>
