<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-01 16:21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 4 Lebanese Civilians Wounded in Israeli Air Raid </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT, June 1 (Xinhua) -- Four villagers were wounded when
Israeli fighter-bombers rocketed suspected guerrilla bases in
south Lebanon at the sunset, security sources in south Lebanon
reported.
</P>
<P>
Israeli jets carried out two consecutive rounds of bombing
at targets at Iglim Al-Toffah, a mountain area some 60
kilometers southeast of Beirut, which is often used by Muslim
guerrillas as a springboard to launch attacks on Israeli
forces in south Lebanon's border strip.
</P>
<P>
In the second bombing round, the Israeli warplanes fired
four air-to-surface missiles at vicinities of Majdal Salim,
wounding four villagers.
</P>
<P>
The security sources said that the two civilians seriously
wounded have been hospitalized and the two others were slightly
injured.
</P>
<P>
The air raid was accompanied by violent bombardment of
Israeli artillery at the heights, according to the anonymous
sources.
</P>
<P>
Guerrillas of the Lebanese pro-Iranian Hezbollah, or Party of
God, announced that they attacked the Israeli outposts of Bir
Kalab and Sojoud with rocket-propelled grenades and machine-guns
at noon today. But no casualties were mentioned in a Hezbollah
statement.
</P>
<P>
Israeli jet fighters carried out 26 air raids at guerrilla
targets in south Lebanon in May, and Israeli helicopters
launched other four air strikes, according to a statistics
made by the security sources.
</P>
<P>
Four Israeli soldiers, including two officers, were killed and
11 wounded in fightings with Muslim guerrillas on the last
battlefront of the Arab-Israeli conflict last month, bringing the
Israeli casualties in south Lebanon to nine killed and 43 wounded
since the beginning of this year.
</P>
<P>
Eleven members of the Israeli-backed South Lebanon Army militia
were also wounded in the same month, adding the casualties
of the Israeli client militia to six killed and 33 injured.
</P>
<P>
The Lebanese resistance movement, on the other hand, lost
seven guerrillas in the same period, making the number of
its martyrs in this year up to 16. 
</P>
</TEXT>
