<HEADLINE> Ethiopian Prime Minister Leaves for Harare </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, June 1 (Xinhua) -- Ethiopian Prime Minister Meles
Zenawi left here today for Harare, Zimbabwe to attend the 33rd
summit meeting of the Organization of African Unity (OAU) which
is due to open on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The heads of state and government of African countries are
expected to deliberate on the agenda the OAU ministerial session
has adopted.
</P>
<P>
The summit is due to discuss among other issues, the situation
in the Great Lakes region, the coup in Sierra Leone and the
developments in Somalia and Angola.
</P>
<P>
Meles was seen off at the Bole International Airport here by
senior government officials.  
</P>
</TEXT>
