<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Zambian President Leaves for OAU Summit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, June 1 (Xinhua) -- Zambian President Frederick Chiluba
left here today for the annual summit of the Organization of
African Unity (OAU) to begin in Harare, the capital of Zimbabwe,
on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Before leaving Lusaka International Airport, Chiluba said that
democracy by the ballot should be encouraged because it helps
leaders rule by the people's decision.
</P>
<P>
He also said that those who want to take power by the gun
should be shown that the democracy by the ballot is better than
through bullets.
</P>
<P>
Referring to the new developments in Sierra Leone, he
expressed his hope that the OAU will help restore constitutional
rule in the country, where elected-president Ahmed Tejan Kabbah
was overthrown on May 25 in a coup.
</P>
<P>
Chiluba said that the three-day OAU summit must show that the
African continent is serious about democracy by condemning the
coup in Sierra Leone. 
</P>
</TEXT>
