<BODY>
<HEADLINE> ANC Welcomes Buthelezi's Remarks on Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, June 1 (Xinhua) -- The African National Congress
(ANC) of South Africa today said it was encouraged by statement
by Inkatha Freedom Party (IFP)leader Mangosuthu Buthelezi on
possible cooperation between the two parties.
</P>
<P>
The ANC gave its unequivocal support to all current efforts
aimed at achieving peace and stability in South Africa, a
statement issued by the ruling party said.
</P>
<P>
The ANC was responding to a report in today's Sunday Times
that Buthelezi had given his stamp of approval to moves to unite
the ANC and IFP, which is representing eight million Zulu tribe
population in the country.
</P>
<P>
The ANC said recognition of the rights of people to support or
belong to political parties of their choice, without hindrance
from traditional authorities or any government bodies, is an
essential element in attaining peace and stability.
</P>
<P>
The ANC announced that it would now be left to the structures
and constituencies of the two parties to decide if the IFP peace
efforts would lay the basis for further advancement and
cooperation between them. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
