<HEADLINE> Ethiopia's Sugar Factory Increases Output This </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, June 1 (Xinhua) -- Ethiopia's Metehara Sugar
Factory produced a record of 110,000 tons of sugar this fiscal
year, the largest in the factory's 25 history.
</P>
<P>
According to a report here today, this year's production
increased by nine percent compared to 101,000 tons of last year.
</P>
<P>
The factory, making a 40 million Birr (about 6 million
Dollars) profit last fiscal year, is expected to make more profit
this fiscal year ending July 7, 1997.
</P>
<P>
The factory officials attributed the success to good
management, good cane harvest and an enthusiastic workforce of
the factory and the plantation.
</P>
<P>
The factory was established in 1972 with over 10,000 workers
and 10,000 hectares of irrigated cane plantation. 
</P>
