<HEADLINE> Nujoma Re-elected as Namibian President </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, June 1 (Xinhua) -- Sam Nujoma was unanimously
re-elected as Namibian president for third term today at the
congress of the ruling South West African People's Organization
(SWAPO), Namibian radio reported.
</P>
<P>
Nujoma took Namibian presidency since 1990. Prior to his
latest re-election, Nujoma was re-elected as president in
December 1994.
</P>
<P>
It is reported that the endorsement of Nujoma's third term in
office will require a constitution amendment.
</P>
<P>
In the just concluded SWAPO congress, the second since
Namibia's independence in 1990, Hendrik Witbooi retained the
vice-presidency, while Fisheries and Marine Resources Minister
Hifikepeunye Pohamba was elected as new party secretary-general,
the report said.
</P>
<P>
About 500 delegates from Namibia's 13 regions attended the
5-day meeting. 
</P>
</TEXT>
