<HEADLINE> First International Forum on Leadership Opens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
AMMAN, June 1 (Xinhua) -- The first international forum on
leadership opened here today with participation of more than 155
delegates from over 80 countries.
</P>
<P>
The forum is organized by the United Nations University
(UNU)/International Leadership Academy (ILA) and inaugurated by
Jordanian Queen Noor.
</P>
<P>
Five major topics will be covered by the program: the U.N. and
the challenges of global leadership, leadership skills and
attitudes, peace and security, south-south leadership and
international leadership.
</P>
<P>
Leaders from the United Nations Education, Scientific and
Cultural Organization, the United Nations Secretariat, the United
Nations Population Fund, the United Nations Truce Supervision
Organization and the World Bank are expected to make speeches
during the program.
</P>
<P>
Former Israeli prime minister Shimon Peres is scheduled to
give a lecture on "leadership and peace and security in
the Middle East" during the meeting.
</P>
<P>
Egyptian Foreign Minister Amr Mousa and Senior Political
Advisor to Egyptian President Hosni Mubarak Osama El-Baz are
also among the speakers.
</P>
<P>
The audience at the leadership program includes individuals
in positions of leadership selected from 650 applicants from
over 80 countries. They are government officials, diplomats,
doctors, lawyers, environmentalists, university professors, directors
of international programs and women activists.
</P>
<P>
To hold such a program was first proposed 16 years ago
by Jordan's incumbent Prime Minister Abdul Salam Majali, who
attended today's opening ceremony and will be one of Jordan's
delegates to the program. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
