<HEADLINE> HK Handover Official Celebration Events Announced </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 2 (Xinhua) -- The schedule of official
celebration events to be staged on July 1 marking Hong Kong's
handover to China and the establishment of the Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region (HKSAR) was announced today by the HKSAR
Chief Executive's Office.
</P>
<P>
The announcement said the State Council of the People's
Republic of China will invite about 4,400 international and local
dignitaries to attend the Ceremony for the establishment of the
HKSAR and the Inauguration of the HKSAR Government at 1.30 a.m. in
Hall 3 of the Hong Kong Convention and Exhibition Center (HKCEC).
</P>
<P>
The Chief Executive, principal officials, members of the
Executive Council, members of the Provisional Legislative Council
and judges of the Court of Final Appeal and the High Court will be
sworn into office during the ceremony, which will last for about
45 minutes.
</P>
<P>
The SAR Government will return to Hall 3 at 10 a.m. to host an
SAR Government Celebration for about 4,600 guests. The Chinese
leader will be invited to make a speech after which the Chief
Executive, Tung Chee Hwa, will deliver his inaugural address.
</P>
<P>
Several ceremonial proceedings will follow, including the
handover of the SAR Land Fund and the presentation of gifts from
31 mainland provinces, autonomous regions and municipalities
directly under the Central Government.
</P>
<P>
A program of cultural events will follow, starting with Tan Dun
conducting the world premiere of his work "Symphony 1997: Heaven,
Earth, Mankind", which he composed to celebrate the handover.
Renowned performers Yo Yo Ma, Jackie Cheung, the Yip's Children
Choir and the Asian Youth Orchestra will join Tan Dun in the
performance.
</P>
<P>
The program will last for an hour and a half, with local
musical talent, multimedia images and visual effects incorporated
in the grand finale.
</P>
<P>
From 4 p.m. to 5 p.m., the SAR Government will be host to some
5,000 guests at a cocktail reception in the Grand Hall of the
HKCEC.
</P>
<P>
The harbor will light up in a blaze of excitement between 9
p.m. and 10 p.m., when the Better Hong Kong Foundation presents
the Hong Kong '97 Spectacular.
</P>
<P>
This seaborne parade and fireworks display is not an official
event but will be a striking conclusion to the day's activities,
the announcement said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
