<DOCNO> XIE19970602.0040 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Seagate Wuxi's New Facility to Start Production Soon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 2 (Xinhua) -- An executive officer of the
Singapore-based regional office of the Seagate Technology, Inc.
said here today that the company's new facility in Wuxi, east
China, may start production at the end of this month after new
investment has been put into the firm.
</P>
<P>
Eddie Lui, Seagate Technology Inc.'s vice-president and
managing director of manufacturing in China, also said he predicts
no change in Seagate's operation in China after Hong Kong's
handover, which is less than a month away.
</P>
<P>
The new building next to the existing facility in the
Wuxi-Singapore Industrial Park represents an investment of 32
million U.S. dollars for equipment and renovation.
</P>
<P>
The disc manufacturing currently in the existing Wuxi facility
will then be moved into the new building.
</P>
<P>
The original facility will start producing E-blocks -- a main
component of disc drives -- in July, with a full daily capacity of
25,000 units.
</P>
<P>
Seagate Technology Shenzhen, Seagate's other facility in China,
has up to now produced 10 million disc drives.
</P>
<P>
The Shenzhen facility took four years to ship its five million
drives and only 10 months to ship another five million. "This is
a clear reflection of the progress that has been made at the
facility in both process and productivity," said Lui.
</P>
<P>
The Shenzhen facility's main products are 1.2 Gbyte, 1.7 Gbyte
and 2.1 Gbyte disc drives designed for desktop computers.
</P>
<P>
Seagate Shenzhen, set up in 1992, has won several awards from
China's central and local governments and various departments.
</P>
<P>
Lui said he is not worried that Hong Kong's handover could
cause any impact on his company's business in China. "We've
increased our investment in Wuxi and our operation in Shenzhen
continues to run quite smoothly. I don't see any impact on our
business by the handover," he said.
</P>
<P>
"In my personal view, things will even be better. I don't see
you'll be in any risk going into China on the expansion of
investment," he concluded.
</P>
<P>
Seagate Technology, Inc, based in the Scotts Valley, California
of the United States, is a leading data technology company
providing products for storing, managing and accessing digital
information.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
