<HEADLINE> Seminar on Sino-Russian Twin Cities Ends </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, June 2 (Xinhua) -- A Chinese official said here today
that communication between twin cities in China and Russia will be
developed in a concrete way.
</P>
<P>
The two countries have already set up 50 twin cities, but there
is still great potential in developing them, said Su Guang, vice
president of the Chinese People's Association for Friendship with
Foreign Countries, during a meeting with Ivan Arkhipov, honorary
president of the Russia-China Friendship Society.
</P>
<P>
Arkhipov, 90, who lived and worked in China for many years,
said that the two countries should fill a historical gap in the
development of Russia-China relations through cooperation,
especially over the economy and in science and technology.
</P>
<P>
Su and Arkhipov met at the end of a week-long seminar on twin
cities between China and Russia, where representatives from the
two countries exchanged views on the establishment and development
of twin cities. 
</P>
</TEXT>
