<HEADLINE> HK Handover Ceremony to Begin at 11:30 on June 30 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 2 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong's handover ceremony is
scheduled to begin at 11:30 p.m. on June 30 in the Hong Kong
Convention and Exhibition Center (HKCEC) Extension with the
presence of 4,000 invited guests, a Hong Kong government official
said here today.
</P>
<P>
In addition to the representatives of Britain and China,
ministers of over 40 countries and secretaries-general and senior
representatives of over 40 international organizations will be
present, Stephen Lam, director of the Handover Ceremony
Coordination Office (HCCO) under the Hong Kong government, told a
press conference.
</P>
<P>
The ceremony will last about 30 to 45 minutes. It will be
followed by the ceremonial departure of the senior British
representatives, Lam said.
</P>
<P>
The format of the ceremony was agreed between Britain and China
last September and includes the lowering of the Union and Hong
Kong flags and the raising of the flags of China and the Hong Kong
Special Administrative Region.
</P>
<P>
Lam also revealed details of some related events on June 30.
</P>
<P>
At about 4:30 p.m., Governor Chris Patten will leave Government
House. Prior to this, there will be a short ceremony during which
the Governor's standard will be lowered from the portico of
Government House.
</P>
<P>
From 6:15 p.m. to 7:30 p.m., a farewell ceremony will take
place at the East Tamar site on the waterfront to mark the end of
British administration in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Following the farewell ceremony, foreign dignitaries and
several thousand guests attending the event will proceed to the
HKCEC Extension for a pre-banquet reception starting at 7:45 p.m.
A spectacular 22-minute fireworks display will light up Victoria
Harbor beginning at around 8:15 p.m. The pre-handover banquet
will begin at about 9:15 p.m.
</P>
<P>
According to Lam, over 8,400 media personnel, representing some
750 media organizations all over the world have applied for
covering the handover ceremony.
</P>
<P>
A press and broadcast center located at HKCEC will be
operational from June 15 to July 10. 
</P>
