<HEADLINE> Winter Snow Hits Mongolia's Livestock Herd </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ULAN BATOR, June 2 (Xinhua) -- The number of fully grown
animals in Mongolia fell by 287,200 during the first five months
of this year, following a drop of 190,500 in the same period last
year, the Mongolian News Agency said today.
</P>
<P>
The report attributed the losses to last winter's heavy snow
falls. The five provinces of Bayan-Olgii, Govi-Altai, Suhebaatar,
Dornovovi and Hovd, which were hit hardest by the bad weather,
accounted for two thirds of the deaths.
</P>
<P>
Another report said today that up to the end of May, a 98
percent survival rate for newborn animals had led to 6.8 million
new additions to the country's livestock herd.
</P>
<P>
Animal husbandry is Mongolia's single most important
agricultural sector. In 1996, the country boasted a record 29.3
million livestock animals. 
</P>
</TEXT>
