<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-02 15:19 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> AL Condemns Continued Turkish Incursion Into Iraq </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, June 2 (Xinhua) -- The Arab League (AL) today strongly
condemned continued Turkish military incursion into northern Iraq
and called for an immediate troop withdrawal.
</P>
<P>
The Cairo-based organization in a statement issued today
expressed its deep concern over the latest developments resulting
from the "wide-scale Turkish military incursion into the depth of
Iraq."
</P>
<P>
"Ankara should withdraw its troops immediately from these
territories and refrain from such breaches of the Iraqi lands and
the sovereignty of the state of Iraq," the statement said.
</P>
<P>
Backed by air bombing and artillery fire, about 25,000 to
50,000 Turkish troops have pushed across the border into northern
Iraq, assaulting rebels of Turkey's separatists of the Kurdish
Workers' Party (PKK) since mid-May.
</P>
<P>
"The continuation of this aggression adversely impacts on the
historical ties of friendship and cooperation between the Arab
countries and Turkey," it added.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, in a report sent to the Egyptian Foreign Ministry,
Turkish Ambassador here Yacar Yakic defended the joint
Turkish-Israeli military exercises and Ankara's military actions
in northern Iraq.
</P>
<P>
Egyptian Assistant Foreign Minister for Arab Affairs Sayed Abu
Zeid, who received the memorandum, reaffirmed Egypt's position on
the two issues.
</P>
<P>
Egypt has criticized the Turkish military incursion into Iraq
and demanded an explanation for its planned massive military
drills with Israel in the Mediterranean this summer, which is
reportedly targeted at Israel's arch foes, Iran and Syria.
</P>
<P>
However, Turkey today termed Arab reactions to Ankara's
military operations in northern Iraq as "unjustifiable."
</P>
<P>
A spokesman of the Turkish Foreign Ministry said that Arab
countries had to understand what he termed as "Turkish fears"
emanating from the terrorist activities perpetrated by the PKK
in northern Iraq.
</P>
<P>
"Turkey has declared, from the start, its respect of Iraq's
territorial integrity and its forces will be withdrawn
immediately after terrorism is wiped out in the region," he added.
</P>
</TEXT>
