<HEADLINE> EU Approves Better Market Access for Poorest Countries </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, June 2 (Xinhua) -- The European Union (EU) today
moved to give the world's poorest countries better access to the
lucrative European market.
</P>
<P>
The foreign ministers of the 15 EU member nations outlined a
short and medium-term strategy aimed at giving the poorest
countries preferential terms for market access.
</P>
<P>
The EU said the decision placed the EU at the forefront of
those developed countries seeking to help the poorest countries
develop their economy.
</P>
<P>
Sir Leon Brittan, the EU trade commissioner, praised the
move. "The Council has shown how determined Europe is to make the
integration of the poorest countries into world trade a reality,"
he said.
</P>
<P>
He also urged the EU's partner countries, including the most
advanced developing countries, to open their markets to the
poorest countries. 
</P>
