<HEADLINE> Chinese President Meets With Head of Vietnamese News Agency </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 2 (Xinhua) -- President Jiang Zemin, meeting with
Ho Tien Nghi, Director General of the Viet Nam News Agency, said
that he hopes that the two countries would continue their efforts
to raise the relations between the two parties and two countries
to a new level.
</P>
<P>
Jiang, who is also general secretary of the Chinese Communist
Party Central Committee, said that China and Viet Nam are joined
by common mountains and rivers, and the friendship between the
people of the two countries goes back to ancient times.
</P>
<P>
Exchanges and co-operation between the two sides in politics,
economy, and culture have been restored and developed since the
normalization of diplomatic relations between the two countries in
1991, the Chinese leader added.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said that there have been frequent exchanges of visits
between leaders of two countries in recent years, and this has
played an important role in furthering the friendship and
cooperation between the two parties and two countries.
</P>
<P>
China and Viet Nam have the same social system and the
conditions of the two countries are similar, both adhere to
socialist road and the leadership of the Communist party, and
adhere to taking economic construction as the central task, Jiang
said.
</P>
<P>
Jiang emphasized that further consolidate and develop the
existing friendship and co-operation between the two countries not
only accords with the fundamental interests of the two countries,
but also is conducive to peace, stability, and development in the
Asia-Pacific region, particularly in the Southeast Asian region.
</P>
<P>
The news agencies of the two countries have established close
links and have had good cooperation in recent years, Jiang noted,
adding that this has served as a bridge for enhancing mutual
understanding and promoting the overall, stable development of
the good-neighborly ties between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Jiang also briefed the visitors on Hong Kong's return to the
motherland and China's economic construction.
</P>
<P>
Ho Tien Nghi said he is grateful for the meeting with Jiang and
has witnessed that the Chinese people have adhered to the reforms
and opening-up amd have achieved tremendous successes in politics,
economy, and culture under the leadership of Chinese Communist
Party.
</P>
<P>
He said that his delegation will tell the Vietnamese people
about what it has seen here in China and further improve mutual
understanding and friendship.
</P>
<P>
Guo Chaoren, President of Xinhua News Agency, was among those
present at the meeting.
</P>
<P>
Ho Tien Nghi and his delegation are here as guests of Xinhua
News Agency.  
</P>
</TEXT>
