<HEADLINE> Young People's Photo Exhibition In Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 2 (Xinhua) -- An exhibition of more than 100
photos taken by children between the ages of 9 and 14, in
Shaoxing County, east China's Zhejiang Province, opened at the
China Art Gallery in Beijing today.
</P>
<P>
The six-day exhibition is sponsored by the Chinese Association
of Women Photographers, the Children's Department of the All-China
Women's Federation, and the Education Commission of Shaoxing
County.
</P>
<P>
Some well-known photographers including Lu Houmin, Hou Bo, and
Xu Xiaobing attended the opening ceremony and took a group photo
with young amateur photographers from Beijing middle schools.
</P>
<P>
The photos provide a vivid depiction of rural life and show the
unsophisticated personalities of rural children, Hou Bo, who is
chairman of the Chinese Association of Women Photographers, noted.
</P>
<P>
The county is known as the "home of little photographers"
because it began training children in photography a decade
ago. There are now more than 1,000 children participating in more
than a hundred photo organizations in the county, whose works have
often won national prizes. 
</P>
</TEXT>
