<HEADLINE> Chinese Premier Speaks Highly of OAU </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 2 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Premier Li Peng Sunday
spoke highly of the remarkable efforts made by the Organization of
African Unity (OAU) to the national independence and political
liberation of Africa.
</P>
<P>
In a congratulatory message to the OAU's 33rd annual session
which opened today in the Zimbabwean capital, Harare, Li described
the OAU as a regional organization drawing great attention from
the international community.
</P>
<P>
"In recent years, the OAU has made gratifying achievements in
maintaining regional stability and promoting economic cooperation,
actively dedicated itself to upholding the rightful interests of
Africa and developing countries and made unremitting efforts in
promoting the establishment of a new international political and
economic order at an early date," Li said in the message.
</P>
<P>
Owing to the concerted efforts of African countries, the
political situation in Africa has, on the whole, moved toward
relaxation, the premier added.
</P>
<P>
He said that he hopes African countries would further
strengthen solidarity and cooperation and score greater successes
in the process of seeking stability and development.
</P>
<P>
Li also mentioned his recent seven-nation Africa tour and said
that the Chinese government and people have all along been
committed to promoting Sino-African friendship and cooperation.
</P>
<P>
"China is ready to even work more closely with African
countries to develop their traditional friendship, expand
mutually beneficial cooperation and strive for the attainment of
common development and the establishment of a just and equitable
new international order," Li said. 
</P>
