<DOCNO> XIE19970602.0071 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Beijing Succeeds In Breeding Golden Monkeys </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 2 (Xinhua) -- The Beijing Zoo announced today
that it has succeeded in breeding a Yunnan golden monkey.
</P>
<P>
The Yunnan golden monkey, which is a rare animal recognized by
animal protection organizations worldwide, is listed along with
the Sichuan and Guizhou golden monkeys, of southwest China, as
being under Class-A state protection.
</P>
<P>
It lives in the Baima natural reserve 1,800 meters to 3,200
meters above sea level in southwest China's Yunnan province, and
lives on leaves, flowers, and fruits.
</P>
<P>
There are about 2,000 golden monkeys in existence. In China's
170 zoos, only the Kunming and Beijing zoos have Yunnan golden
monkeys.
</P>
<P>
The new baby golden monkey, now one month old, is doing well
and has been seen by visitors to the zoo together with its
mother.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970602.0072 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Romania, Ukraine Sign Friendship Treaty </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, June 2 (Xinhua) -- Romanian President Emil
Constantinescu and his Ukrainian counterpart Leonid Kuchma today
signed a historic friendship treaty.
</P>
<P>
Constantinescu said that the treaty ensures peace, cooperation
and stability to the peoples of both countries.
</P>
<P>
Kuchma said the signing of the treaty was a major step in
strengthening relations between Ukraine and Romania. It was a sign
that their relationship had entered a new era of partnership.
</P>
<P>
Under the 10-year pact, signed in the Black Sea resort of
Neptun, Romania and Ukraine recognize the present delineation of
their common border and the integrity of each other's territories,
thus formalizing the attribution to Kiev of territory ceded to the
Soviet Union under a 1939 secret Nazi-Soviet pact.
</P>
<P>
The infamous pact between Nazi Germany's foreign minister
Joachim von Ribbentrop and his Soviet counterpart Vyacheslav
Molotov led to the carving up of Poland and allowed Moscow to
acquire Romania's northern Bukovina and the territory then known
as Bessarabia.
</P>
<P>
During negotiations for the friendship treaty, Romania insisted
the secret accord be condemned in the text, but Ukraine refused.
</P>
<P>
Last month, the Romanian government said that it was ready to
make concessions in order to promote regional stability and to
support its application for NATO membership.
</P>
<P>
Romania wanted the treaty to be concluded before the Madrid
NATO summit on July 8-9 which will name the first eastern
European countries to be invited into the Western military
alliance.
</P>
<P>
Romania hopes to be among the first wave of countries to join
NATO.
</P>
<P>
The foreign ministers of the two countries also signed a
document today on the outstanding issues, which include the
demarcation of the Black Sea continental shelf and the
determination of the status of Snake Island.
</P>
<P>
The document is included in the treaty as an appendix.
</P>
<P>
Romania's media said that the two sides will forward these
issues to the International Court of Justice in the Hague,
Netherlands, for arbitration if they are not sorted out
bilaterally. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
