<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Photo Exhibition on HK Return Opens in Colombo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, June 2 (Xinhua) -- A seven-day photo exhibition on
Hong Kong's return to China was opened here today by the Chinese
Embassy in Sri Lanka.
</P>
<P>
The show includes 99 pictures depicting Hong Kong's history,
exchanges between Hong Kong and China's mainland, the process of
Hong Kong's return to the motherland and Hong Kong today.
</P>
<P>
Sri Lankan Minister of Cultural and Religious Affairs Lakshman
Jayakody and other government officials attended the opening
ceremony.
</P>
<P>
Chen Defu, Chinese ambassador to Sri Lanka, said that Hong Kong
has been part of China since ancient times and it is the sacred
mission of the whole Chinese nation to recover Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
He said that on July 1, 1997, China will resume the exercise of
sovereignty over Hong Kong, putting an end to British colonial
rule that has lasted for more than 150 years.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong will come back into the embrace of the motherland in
29 days, which is not only a grand occasion for the Chinese
nation, but also a great event attracting worldwide attention, he
noted.
</P>
<P>
Chen pointed out that the Chinese government and its people are
bound to take a prosperous and stable Hong Kong into the 21st
century.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
