<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Jordan, Bahrain to Enhance Economic Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
AMMAN, June 2 (Xinhua) -- Jordan today expressed its hope to
strengthen economic ties with Bahrain as the first ever Bahraini
trade exhibition opened here today.
</P>
<P>
This remark was made by Jordanian Prime Minister Abdul-Salam
Majali while meeting a Bahraini delegation today.
</P>
<P>
Majali said that Jordan wants to develop further bilateral
ties in all fields with Bahrain, particularly in trade and
economic cooperation.
</P>
<P>
The Bahraini guests are here in an attempt to establish joint
ventures with the Arab kingdom, and hold the five-day exhibition,
a local radio report said.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition was organized to reactivate the free trade
agreement signed by the two countries in 1995, said Bahraini
Ambassador to Jordan Mohammad Ben Saif Jaber Musalam at a press
conference Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Around 50 Bahraini industrial companies were present at the
exhibition and some Jordanian-Bahraini projects will be
forthcoming, according to local officials.
</P>
<P>
Jordan seeks better access to the Gulf Cooperation Council
(GCC) countries' markets through the implementation of its
agreement with Bahrain, said Musalam.
</P>
<P>
The GCC is a regional political, economic and military
organization grouping Saudi Arabia, Kuwait, the United Arab
Emirates, Oman, Bahrain and Qatar. 
</P>
</TEXT>
