<HEADLINE> Qian Zhengying Meets With Laotian-Chinese Friendship Association </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 2 (Xinhua) -- Qian Zhengying, vice-chairwoman of
the National Committee of the Chinese People's Political
Consulative Conference (CPPCC), in a meeting with a delegation
from the Lao-Chinese Friendship Association today, said that China
and Laos should keep learning from each other in their economic
development drive.
</P>
<P>
During their meeting in Beijing's Great Hall of the People,
Qian told the group, which was led by its president Xaysomphone
Phomvihane, that the two countries are good neighbors that are
linked by mountains and rivers and that the governments and
peoples of the two countries have always supported and helped each
other in the past.
</P>
<P>
China is delighted to see every achievement scored by the
Laotian people in their reform and opening up drive under the
leadership of the Laotian People's Revolutionary Party and the
Laotian government, she said.
</P>
<P>
She added that the Laotian-Chinese Friendship Association has
played a significant role in promoting exchanges, co-operation and
friendship between the two peoples.
</P>
<P>
She said she hopes the Laotian guests will gain a better
understanding of the specific conditions in various areas in
China during their visit.
</P>
<P>
Phomvihane said that the two peoples share a long tradition of
friendship, and that the Laotian People's Revolutionary Party and
the government highly appreciate the assistance they have received
from the Communist Party of China, the Chinese government, and the
Chinese people.
</P>
<P>
He pledged to develop the bilateral friendly co-operative
relations that the older generation of leaders of the two
countries have forged.
</P>
<P>
He expressed the hope that the delegation will learn from
China's experience in the reform and opening up during its
visit. 
</P>
