<HEADLINE> Taliban-1stadd: Taliban Close Iranian Embassy in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, June 2 (Xinhua) -- The Afghan Islamic militia
Taliban today closed the Iranian Embassy in Kabul and ordered the
diplomats to leave the country within 48 hours, reports reaching
here quoted an official statement as saying.
</P>
<P>
The statement accused the Iranian diplomats of creating
disturbances among the people of Afghanistan, according to the
reports.
</P>
<P>
"In view of the hostile deeds by the authorities of the Islamic
Republic of Iran ... the Foreign Ministry of the Islamic State of
Afghanistan decided to temporarily close the Iranian Embassy in
Kabul and to expel all its Iranian staff within 48 hours," the
statement said.
</P>
<P>
"According to undeniable evidences, the Islamic Republic of
Iran interfered, through its Kabul embassy staff, in the Afghan
internal affairs and sought to disrupt the peaceful atmosphere and
brotherly relations existing between Kabul citizens," it added.
