<HEADLINE> Sensitive Index on BSE Gains 53.08 Points </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, June 2 (Xinhua) -- The Sensitive index on the Bombay
Stock Exchange (BSE) market today gained 53.08 points to 3,808.18
as against last weekend's close of 3,755.10.
</P>
<P>
The national index also shot up by 21.97 points to 1,634.17
from 1,612.20 last weekend.
</P>
<P>
The BSE-200 and US dollar index finished at 365.95 and 170.28
compared to 361.40 and 168.12 last weekend.
</P>
<P>
Speculatives forged ahead on the opening day of the new account
on the BSE market today on fresh buying support from local
operators and foreign institutional investors.
</P>
<P>
The BSE sensitive index started better at 3,758.39 today,
gradually moved upwards to cross the 3,800-mark and closed at
3,808.18.
</P>
<P>
Marketmen said the market was bottomed out and expected an
upward trend during the week with major corporates announcing good
working results.  
</P>
