<HEADLINE> Romania, Ukraine Sign Friendship Treaty </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, June 2 (Xinhua) -- Romanian President Emil
Constantinescu and his Ukrainian counterpart Leonid Kuchma today
signed a historic treaty on good-neighborly and cooperative
relations between their two countries.
</P>
<P>
Under the pact signed in the Black Sea resort of Neptun, the
Romania and Ukraine recognize the common borders between them and
the integrity of each other's territories.
</P>
<P>
Constantinescu said that the treaty ensures peace, cooperation
and stability to the peoples of the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Kuchma said that the signing of the treaty is a major step
toward strengthening relations between Ukraine and Romania. It
marked the relationship between the two countries has entered a
new era of partnership, he added. 
