<HEADLINE> Sierra Leone Sprinter Dove-Edwin Reinstated </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, June 2 (Xinhua) -- Horace Dove-Edwin of Sierra Leone was
granted a request for an early reinstatement, the International
Amateur Atheletic Federation said in Monaco on Monday.
</P>
<P>
In a statement, the IAAF said its council had accepted a
request from the sprinter for an early reinstatement.
</P>
<P>
Dove-Edwin was tested positive for stanozolol at the 1994
Commonwealth Games where he finished second in the 100 meters.
</P>
<P>
"He was living in the United States and was unable to get a
hearing in Sierra Leone until early this year," IAAF spokesman
Giorgio Reineri said. "Their federation upheld the ban but
recommended an early reinstatement." 
