<HEADLINE> Brazilian Kuerten Books Last Quarter-final Berth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, June 2 (Xinhua) -- Brazilian Gustavo Kuerten won a
protracted match over Ukrainian Andrei Medvedev to book the last
quarterfinal berth of the French Open here on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Kuerten, 20, survived the competition after two hours and 45
minutes to win the match 5-7, 6-1, 6-2, 1-6, 7-5, which was
adjourned late Sunday at 2-2 in the fifth set due to fading light.
</P>
<P>
Kuerten who defeated 1995 champion Thomas Muster in the
third-round, will play defending champion Yevgeny Kafelnikov of
Russia for a semi-final spot.
</P>
<P>
Medvedev, 22, was under increasing pressure from the flashing
returns of Kuerten.
</P>
<P>
"It is unbelievable to win this match," said Kuerten, the first
Brazilian to reach the quarter-finals at Roland Garros since Tomas
Koch was beaten in the last eight in 1968. 
</P>
