<HEADLINE> Qian Zhengying Meets With Syrian-Chinese Friendship Delegation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 2 (Xinhua) -- Qian Zhengying, vice-chairwoman of
the National Committee of the Chinese People's Political
Consultative Conference (CPPCC), said today that Sino-Syrian
friendly relations have grown steadily despite dramatic changes in
the international situation since the two countries established
diplomatic relations 41 years ago.
</P>
<P>
Qian made the remark in a meeting with a Syrian-Chinese
Friendship Association delegation.
</P>
<P>
She told the delegation, which was lead by Jasem Mousa, that
the Chinese people cherish friendly feelings for the Syrian
people, and that the Chinese government has always paid close
attention to the development of relations with Syria and other
Middle East countries.
</P>
<P>
She said that the Chinese government and people are grateful
to Syria for its support to China on the human rights issue.
</P>
<P>
She added that China appreciates Syria's consistent adherence
to the "one China" stand on the Taiwan issue.
</P>
<P>
She said the current international situation requires that the
two countries further promote co-operation. She expressed the
belief that the visit by the Syrian delegation will enhance
understanding and friendship between the peoples of the two
countries.
</P>
<P>
On the Middle East issue, she said that the Chinese government
and the Chinese people have always supported the just demands
of the Arab people, and that they believe the problems in the region
should be resolved politically on the basis of relevant UN
resolutions.
</P>
<P>
She said she hopes all parties in the region will continue to
adopt a flexible and practical attitude in their efforts to
realize peace and stability in the Middle East at an early date.
</P>
<P>
Mousa said that he is delighted to see the tremendous
achievements that China has made in its economic development, and
that he is delighted to see that Hong Kong will soon return to the
motherland.
</P>
<P>
He said he hopes the two countries will further promote their
friendly co-operative relations.  
</P>
