<HEADLINE> Miraculous Escape for Saudi Passenger Airlines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, June 2 (Xinhua) -- A Saudi Arabian Airlines Boeing
747 had a miraculous escape today when it landed at a wrong place
in India's southern city of Chennai.
</P>
<P>
Reports reaching here said the flight with at least 327
passengers was to arrive in Chennai, capital of Tamil Nadu, from
Riyadh, landed at a nearby air force station airfield instead of
the international airport. The aircraft, however, made a safe
landing and all passengers were safe.
</P>
<P>
The reasons for the error, which could have led to a major
mishap, could not be ascertained immediately. An airport official
said the pilot apparently mistook the air force airfield for the
runway at the international terminal.
</P>
<P>
Customs and immigration authorities have proceeded to the air
force airfield to escort the passengers to the airport for customs
clearance.  
</P>
