<HEADLINE> Malaysia to Host 1997 Gold Asia Exhibition </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, June 2 (Xinhua) -- The 1997 Gold Asia Exhibition
will be held in Malaysia from November 7 to 9, according to a
statement by the World Gold Council released here today.
</P>
<P>
The council said that Malaysia has been chosen as the venue for
the event because it has been sustaining an economic growth rate
of over eight percent over the last nine years and has emerged as
a regional distribution center and also because of its tax
liberalization, which supports the gold business, Malaysia is
currently one of the largest gold jewelry fabrication centers,
fabricating 100 tons annually, most of which is exported.
</P>
<P>
"We aim to position Gold Asia '97 as a platform to usher in the
gold market for the next millennium. By introducing innovative
gold merchandise into the region and increasing consumer awareness
and knowledge of high caratage products, we believe that this
major event would contribute to the business development of the
gold market in the next millennium," the council said.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition will feature unique gold merchandise by 100
leading manufacturers from Asia, Europe and the Middle East, it
said, adding highlights include an exclusive Gold Jewelry Fashion
Gala featuring the widest range of elegant jewelry from all over
the world.
</P>
<P>
A seminar will be held concurrently with the exhibition to
discuss topics like technology, product development, retailing,
market analysis and deregulation, it said.
</P>
<P>
Asia remains the largest consumer of gold with 1,728 tons,
accounting for 66 percent of the world's total consumption.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
