<HEADLINE> HK Stock Market Index Reaches New Height </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 2 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong stock market reached a
new height here today with the Hang Seng Index (HSI) climbing
223.09 points to close at 14,990.90.
</P>
<P>
The turnover on the local bourse also rose sharply, setting a
new record of 26.479 billion HK dollars (3.42 billion
U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
It is the second time for the HSI and turnover on the Hong Kong
Stock Exchange to break records simultaneously on one trading day
in a period of six trading days.
</P>
<P>
Last Monday, the HSI hit 14,574 while the turnover closed at
20.587 billion HK dollars (2.67 billion U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Stock analysts said that the HSI is expected to surpass the
15,000 point mark before it falls for readjustment.
</P>
<P>
They said that promoted by the news that the HK government will
put two lots of land into auction, today's HSI sub-index
properties rose 416.70 points to 26,590.
</P>
<P>
Utilities, another major sub-index of HSI, for the first time
surged 502 points to reach 17,527. The growth momentum, which
was promoted by China factor, is rarely seen in recent years.
</P>
<P>
The analysts said that the excellent performances of the
China-funded stocks led the hiking of the stocks today and they
forecast that the rising will continue in the period around Hong
Kong's handover at the end of this month. 
</P>
</TEXT>
