<HEADLINE> Urgent: W. African Troops Attack S. Leone </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FREETOWN, June 2 (Xinhua) -- Ground fighting occurred around
the military headquarters in Freetown, capital of Sierra Leone,
today after warships of the west African peacekeeping forces, the
ECOMOG, started bombing the coup makers at dawn.
</P>
<P>
The attack came after last night's failure of a peace
agreement between soldiers who toppled civilian President Ahmed
Kabbah on May 25, and British and Nigerian diplomats. The coup
leaders are based in the camps of the military headquarters.
