<HEADLINE> British Aid to Uganda Amounts to 39 Million </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, June 2 (Xinhua) -- British bilateral aid to Uganda in
the 1996/97 financial year amounted to 39 million pound sterling,
reported the local daily '' The Monitor'' today.
</P>
<P>
The British government has been at the forefront of
modernising the Ugandan police force through training and
provision of technical aid, the poaper said, adding that Uganda's
education sector, civil service and the judiciary have all
benefited from British aid.
</P>
<P>
There exist strong trade relations between Uganda and Britain.
In 1996, Uganda's imports from Britain reached 64 Million Pounds,
while its exports to Britain stood at 15 Million Pounds.
</P>
<P>
Britain has been Uganda's number one donor followed by
Denmark, Germany and the U.S. 
</P>
</TEXT>
