<HEADLINE> New Tree Strain Found in Central China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANCHANG, June 2 (Xinhua) -- Experts recently identified four
maples newly found in a forestry farm in Tonggu county of central
China's Jiangxi Province as a new tree strain, which they named
the "Tonggu Maple."
</P>
<P>
The new strain was first found by a local tree-breeding
technician, Yu Renxing, who for the past six years has observed
the four trees and kept careful records.
</P>
<P>
According to Yu Zhixiong, a well-known flora taxonomist in
China, the finding of Tonggu Maple will play a significant role in
the research of systematic botany.
</P>
<P>
China has more than 100 stains of maple which belong to the
deciduous arbor. 
</P>
