<HEADLINE> China Closing Down Illegal Job Agencies </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 2 (Xinhua) -- A nationwide campaign in China has
closed 1,612 illegal job agencies and ordered nearly 300 others
ordered to halt operations for straightening themselves out,
according to Deputy Labor Minister Lin Yongsan.
</P>
<P>
Lin said that the country's labor departments in cities and
towns have job agencies and there are also 4,700 non-government
institutions and individuals running their own agencies.
</P>
<P>
Last July, the Ministry of Labor, and the State Commerce and
Industry Administration issued a circular about bringing the
job-search business under the administrative controls of the
Ministry of Labor.
</P>
<P>
Since then, administrative offices have closed down illicit
job-agencies and are allowing those that obey the law to continue
to operate.
</P>
<P>
Tax, pricing, public security, personnel, and civil affairs
authorities have offered their help during the campaign, according
to the official.  
</P>
</TEXT>
