Bank Front (WNBF) was moving to its end, said a former WNBF
commander.
</P>
<P>
Moses Gala, one of the top commanders of WNBF, said that only
two detachment commanders remained in the bushes in the
north-west. He made the statements when he spoke to local
businessmen and government troops in the northern city of Gulu
last week.
</P>
<P>
ten high ranking WNBF officers surrendered last week to the
governemnt troops with their subordinates, an earlier report
said.
</P>
<P>
Gala said he is trying to persuade the last two detachment
commanders in the bush to report to local authorities.
</P>
<P>
WNBF, which had operated in southern Sudan, lost its main
forces in March in southern Sudan, and many of its remnants
surrendered to the Ugandan government troops.
</P>
<P>
There were two rebel groups active in the north-west: WNBF and
Uganda National Resque Front, Part Two. Recent reports said many
UNRF II fighters also reported to local authorities. 
