<HEADLINE> Famous Chinese Physicist Dies </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGCHUN, June 2 (Xinhua) -- Yu Ruihuang, a famous Chinese
physicist, died at the age of 91 from illness last month.
</P>
<P>
Yu, an academician of the Chinese Academy of Sciences, devoted
himself to the study of X-ray crystallography and metal
physics. He had been a teacher for nearly 70 years, and trained a
large number of excellent personnel for the country.
</P>
<P>
Yu was the honorary dean of the physics department at Jilin
University, vice-chairman of the Standing Committee of the Jilin
Provincial People's Congress, and member of the Central Committee
of the China Democratic League.  
</P>
