<HEADLINE> Coxsackie Disease Kills 13 in Malaysia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, June 2 (Xinhua) -- Malaysia is seeking
international help to curb Coxsackie B infection which claimed 13
lives in Sarawak, East Malaysia, as of Sunday, Health Minister
Chua Jui Meng said today.
</P>
<P>
He said his government viewed the situation as very serious as
the infection was killing children aged four-years and below and
his ministry had placed news about the disease on the Internet,
hoping medical experts from abroad would respond and help Malaysia
fight the infection.
</P>
<P>
The federal government rushed medical teams and specialists to
Sarawak to contain the disease which had broken out in areas of
Sibu, Sarikei and Kuching of the state, the minister said after
opening the Ministry's Dialogue with professional bodies here.
</P>
<P>
The disease was first reported on April 14 this year in Sibu
where eight children died and it spread to nearby Sarikei where
four other children died while one more death has been reported in
Kuching, according to the minister.  
</P>
