<HEADLINE> Nagano Games Tickets Enjoy Brisk Sale </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, June 2 (Xinhua) -- Tickets for some events at next
year's Nagano Winter Olympics were sold out within minutes of
going on sale in Japan on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Officials said that hundreds of people queued all night in
Nagano in the hope of securing seats for the opening ceremony,
figure skating and ice hockey.
</P>
<P>
But many were turned away disappointed after the tickets were
snapped up within minutes, agents said.
</P>
<P>
The 244,000 tickets that went on sale on Monday represented
some 40 percent of the tickets allotted for advance sale in Japan,
an official from the Nagano Olympic Winter Games Organising
Committee (NAOC) said.
</P>
<P>
Other tickets have been reserved for package tours or for sale
at the door.
</P>
<P>
The organising committee said the brisk sales in Japan, which
has been allotted about 80 percent of the total of 1.2 million
tickets for the Games, would not affect overseas sales which are
handled through agents. 
