<HEADLINE> China Builds Agricultural Machinery Museum </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, June 2 (Xinhua) -- China is displaying its historic
development of agricultural machinery in a new museum in Yuyao
City in east China's Zhejiang Province.
</P>
<P>
The 2,000-sq.m. museum displays over 350 agriculture tools and
machines. They include a wooden windmill made in 201 BC and a
water wagon made in 167 AD as well as the latest agricultural
machinery.
</P>
