<HEADLINE> Hanbo Scandal Defendants Sentenced </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, June 2 (Xinhua) -- The Seoul District Court sentenced Hanbo
Group owner Chung Tae-soo to 15 years in prison in today's trial and
gave three to seven year jail terms to a former cabinet minister, four
politicians and three former bank officials implicated in the Hanbo
bribes-for-loans scandal.
</P>
<P>
In a penalty measurement trial for the 11 defendants related
two weeks ago, prosecutors had demanded 20-year imprisonment for
Chung and five to eight years to the others.
</P>
<P>
Chung has embezzled huge company fund and offered bribes to
government officials, legislators and the bank officials. In
return, Chung has been able to get 5.6 billion U.S. dollar loans
from the banks and other preferences from the administration as
well as the National Assembly.
</P>
<P>
In today's ruling, Chung was found guilty of fraud, embezzlement of
215 million U.S. dollars and bribes of 3.65 million.
</P>
<P>
His son, Hanbo Group chairman Chung Po-keun and company's financial
chief Kim Jong-kook were also pronounced guilty of embezzlement.
</P>
<P>
Ruling New Korea party (NKP) lawmaker Hong In-kil was sentenced to
seven years in jail and fined 11.2 million U.S. dollars for receiving
the same amount in bribes from Chung.
</P>
<P>
Those on trial also include two other NKP lawmakers Hwang Byung-tai
and Chung Jae-chull and opposition lawmaker Kwon Roh-kap of the major
National Congress for New politics (NCNP). They were sentenced three
to five-year imprisonment and fined in the amount they took bribes
from Hanbo Group.
</P>
<P>
Former Home Minister Kim Woo-suk and three former bank heads were
given four to five-year imprisonment.
</P>
<P>
In announcing the sentences, the presiding judge lamented that
irregularities surrounding the Hanbo scandal such as embezzlement,
bribing, taking bribe and credit without responsibility had caused
crisis in society and the national economy.
</P>
<P>
The persons implicated in the scandal should be sternly punished so
as to prevent further politic-business collusion as well as
irregularities and corruption, he added.
</P>
<P>
Eight other politicians indicted for taking bribes from the Hanbo
owner, including Pusan Mayor Moon Jung-soo and two incumbent lawmakers
and five ex-lawmakers, will also go on trial this month. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
