<HEADLINE> Chicago Wins first Match in NBA Final Series </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, June 1 (Xinhua) -- A jump shot from Michael Jordan
in the final seconds lifted the defending champion Chicago Bulls
to an 84-82 victory over Utah Jazz in game one of the National
Basketball Association championship finals in Chicago on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Jordan's parting shot over a helpless Bryon Russell broke an
82-82 tie that he had established with a free throw 30 seconds
earlier.
</P>
<P>
In the interim, Chicago's Dennis Rodman fouled Karl Malone in a
scramble for a rebound to send the NBA's most valuable player to
the free throw line.
</P>
<P>
Malone, whose overall consistency has earned him the nickname
The Mailman, missed both of them with nine seconds remaining.
</P>
<P>
Jordan scored 19 of his 31 points in the second half. Scottie
Pippen, who appeared unhindered by his sore left foot, added 27
for Chicago.
</P>
<P>
The Bulls, who are gunning for their fifth NBA title in seven
years, host the Jazz in game two on Wednesday. Then the
best-of-seven series moves to Salt Lake City. 
</P>
</TEXT>
