<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Military Leader Meets Portuguese Visitor </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 2 (Xinhua) -- Zhang Wannian, vice-chairman of
China's Central Military Commission, in a meeting with visiting
Chief of Staff of Portugal's Air Force Aurelio Benito Aleixo
Corbal, said that China is willing to work with Portugal to bring
bilateral friendly relations into the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
During today's meeting with Corbal at the Great Hall of the
People, Zhang said that relations between the two countries and
armed forces have gone well: "We are very satisfied with it."
</P>
<P>
He added that military leaders of the two countries have had a
frequent exchange of visits in recent years, which promoted
bilateral ties.
</P>
<P>
"Developing Sino-Portuguese friendly relations is not only in
keeping with the fundamental interests of the two countries and
peoples, but also conducive to safeguarding world peace," he noted.
</P>
<P>
Zhang told Corbal that China observes an independent foreign
policy of peace, proposes to advance state-to-state relations
based on the Five Principles of Peaceful Co-existence, and opposes
hegemonism and power politics.
</P>
<P>
He also expressed the belief that Corbal's current visit to
China will push ahead relations between the two countries and
their armed forces.
</P>
<P>
Corbal said that there was a frequent exchange of visits
between leaders of the two armed forces, and that there exist
broad prospects for their further cooperation.
</P>
<P>
He added that his China trip will boost friendly and
cooperative relations between the two coutries and armed forces.
</P>
<P>
Present on the occasion were Commander of the Air Force of the
Chinese People's Liberation Army Liu Shunyao and Portugal's
Ambassador to China Pedro Catarino.
</P>
