<HEADLINE> Shanghai Opens Express Refrigerated Shipping to Japan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, June 2 (Xinhua) -- Two regular express refrigerated
shipping lines between Shanghai, China's leading port city, and
Japan started operation last weekend.
</P>
<P>
One ship sets sail every Friday from Shanghai and arrives at
Yokohama next Monday morning. The other ship sails for Osaka via
Kobe every Saturday and reaches its destination on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The two vessels, owned by the Shanghai Haixin Shipping Co. Ltd
(SHSCL), were made in Holland with each accommodating 228
refrigerated containers.
</P>
<P>
The SHSCL has 180 vessels. It opened the first domestic
shipping line on April 11 and an express container line to Japan
on April 23.  
</P>
