<HEADLINE> China's Bond Trust System to Begin Trial Operation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 2 (Xinhua) -- China will soon initiate a
nationally unified treasury bond trust and settlement system on a
trial basis, today's China Securities quoted an official source as
saying.
</P>
<P>
The Central Treasury Bond Registration and Settlement
Corporation is developing a nationally unified bond trust and
settlement system and the system will soon begin trial operation,
said Wang Yong, general manager of the corporation.
</P>
<P>
The further development of the treasury bond market depends on
market standardization and improvement, construction of basic
market facilities, and risk controls for the bond market, Wang
said at a recent seminar on bond markets across the Taiwan Straits.
</P>
<P>
China's treasury bond market has been developing very rapidly
since the floatation of treasury bonds resumed in 1981. Annual
issues have soared in recent years, from 19 billion yuan (about
2.3 billion US dollars) in 1991 to more than 190 billion yuan last
year. Outstanding government bonds were valued at 440 billion yuan
by the end of 1995.
</P>
<P>
China's bond issue this year is budgeted at 248.5 billion
yuan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
