<HEADLINE> China's National Economy to Register Sound Growth in Second Quarter </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 2 (Xinhua) -- The national economy will maintain
a consistent growth during the second quarter of this year, as the
country's inflation rate steadily declines, according to an
official report released by the State Information Center.
</P>
<P>
The center's report, printed in today's overseas version of the
People's Daily, said that the inflation rate will stand at 1.5
percent in the April-June period. There is no sign of the price
index rebounding over the next few months, though the price hike
for consumer goods for residents kept a comparatively higher
increase margin.
</P>
<P>
The country's financial operation is on a smooth track, with a
balance basically achieved between the financial revenues and
expenditures.
</P>
<P>
The report said that in the second quarter, investment in
state-owned fixed assets will go up by 17 percent, thanks to the
increase in input in technical upgrading and real estate.
</P>
<P>
The export volume is expected to increase by 22.5 percent, a
slower growth rate than the previous quarters, while the increase
of imports stands at 1.5 percent.
</P>
<P>
The industrial growth is estimated to be 15.8 percent for the
second quarter, however, that of the state-owned sector will be
7.8 percent, lagging far behind the country's average.
</P>
<P>
This year, the acreage under crops expanded by 1.6 million ha
on the basis of last year, but grain output could fluctuate this
fall because of the decline in maize planting, according to the
report. 
</P>
</TEXT>
