<HEADLINE> Chinese Lifter Wins 76kg Category at Weightlifting Worlds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAPETOWN, JUNE 1 (Xinhua) -- Chinese strongman Wang Hongyu set
a snatch world youth record and collected three gold medals in the
men's 76kg category at the World Youth Championships here on
Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Wang Hongyu, 18, snatched 155.5 kilograms in his third attempt,
bettering the previous mark set by Russian lifter Sergei Filimonov.
</P>
<P>
After taking the gold in the snatch, Wang Hongyu, who made his
debut in international competitions, jerked 185 kilograms for a
winning total of 340 kilograms.
</P>
<P>
Barkhah Hossein of Iran, who had 150 in the snatch and 180 in
the jerk, finished second in the total with a combined weight of
330 kilograms.
</P>
<P>
Zhou Kai, also from China, had the bronze medal in the total at
325 kilograms, with 145 from snatch and 180 from jerk. 
