<HEADLINE> Hunan Opens First Port of Entry to Foreign Vessels </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGSHA, June 2 (Xinhua) -- A port of entry in Yueyang,
finally completed after 30 years of construction, received the
first foreign cargo vessel just two days ago.
</P>
<P>
Located in central China's Hunan province, Chenglingji port,
which has been approved by the State Council to open to foreign
vessels, will provide the inland province's first passage to the
sea.
</P>
<P>
The port is located at the junction of Dongting Lake and the
Yangtze River, and is adjacent to the Beijing-Guangzhou railway
line and the No. 107 national highway.
</P>
<P>
It now handles more than 40,000 overseas visitors each year. The
annual cargo handling capacities for the port have reached six
million tons.
</P>
<P>
At present, inspection and service departments of the port have
been set up. Authorities say that the new port will play an
important role in Hunan's reform and opening-up drive.  
</P>
