<HEADLINE> Indonesia's Ruling Party Leading in Vote Tally </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, June 2 (Xinhua) -- Indonesia's ruling Golkar party
remains leading in the vote tally from all the 27 provinces in the
country.
</P>
<P>
As of 18:31 p.m. Sunday, the ruling Golkar party has gathered
82,394,419 of the 110,938,069 votes counted or around 74.24
percent.
</P>
<P>
The United Development Party (PPP) came second with 25,135,647
votes (22.66 percent) and the Indonesian Democratic Party (PDI)
3,408,003 votes (3.07 percent).
</P>
<P>
PPP, Golkar and PDI are vying for 425 seats of the house of
representatives. The remaining 75 seats are preserved for the
armed forces whose members do no vote.
</P>
<P>
A total of 124,740,987 people were eligible to vote in the May
29 general election. 
</P>
</TEXT>
