<HEADLINE> Ramos to Visit 7 More Nations This Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, June 2 (Xinhua) -- Untired of his self-proclaimed role
as the Philippines' foremost salesman, President Fidel Ramos will
visit at least seven more countries this year.
</P>
<P>
Ramos will journey to Britain, Greece and Oman by the third
week of this month, although the Presidential Palace has not yet
officially announced his trip to the three countries, local press
reported today.
</P>
<P>
He is also scheduled to fly to Canada toward the latter part of
the year to reciprocate Prime Minister Jean Chretien's state visit
to the Philippines last year, the reports said.
</P>
<P>
While in Canada, the President would also attend the fifth
informal leaders' meeting of the Asia Pacific Economic Cooperation
(APEC) in Vancouver, the reports said.
</P>
<P>
Presidential Palace sources said that before flying to Canada,
the President may make a stopover in New Work to address the
United Nations on population and demographic issues.
</P>
<P>
Foreign Secretary Domingo Siazon disclosed earlier that a trip
to Peru, Argentina and Chile was also being "tentatively
considered".
</P>
<P>
President Ramos has traveled to at least 30 countries and
regions after he came to power in 1998. He described himself the
No.1 salesman of the Philippines, saying his trips abroad had
drawn 20 billion U.S. dollars in investments into the country.
</P>
</TEXT>
