<HEADLINE> Airport in Southest China Gets Approval </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, June 2 (Xinhua) -- Changle International Airport in
Fuzhou, capital of China's Fujian province, recently has passed
initial inspection and is scheduled to open on June 23.
</P>
<P>
The airport is designed to receive all types of aircraft and
handle 6.5 million passengers and 200,000 tons of cargo a
year. The cost of contruction rans into 3.23 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
Local aviation officials say the airline business volume in
Fuzhou has been growing at an annual rate of more than 30 percent
in the past decade. The new airport when operational not only
eases the burden on Yixu Airport of Fuzhou, but also benefits
economic growth in the region and facilitates the preparation for
future direct flights to Taiwan. 
</P>
