<HEADLINE> 400 Filipinos Sentenced to Death in 2 Years </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, June 2 (Xinhua) -- A total of 400 Filipinos have been
sentenced to death since the country re-adopted the capital
punishment two years ago in a bid to curb heinous crimes.
</P>
<P>
However, none of them has been lethally injected to death so
far due to conflicts over who would execute the death sentence,
today's local press reported.
</P>
<P>
According to Senator Ernesto Herrera, a watchdog over the
crimes in the country, most of the convicts are rapists,
murderers, kidnappers, drug dealers and possessors of heavy
illegal firearms.
</P>
<P>
Local media said earlier that the first convict is expected to
be executed in June this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
