<BODY>
<HEADLINE> High-tech Benefits Southern Industrial Zone </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, June 2 (Xinhua) -- The Jinpan Industrial Development
Zone in Hainan province is developing rapidly, as more high-tech
enterprises are settled down there.
</P>
<P>
The zone, one of the first four industrial development areas in
the province, now has 22 high-tech companies, which are mostly
involved in the manufacturing of computer disks, transformers,
industrial antiseptics, automobile addictives and aromatics.
</P>
<P>
Total industrial output value in the zone in the first four
months of this year reached 340 million yuan, an increase of 78
percent over the same period of last year.
</P>
<P>
The zone now has more than 120 enterprises, which do business
in electronics, building materials, textiles, food, medicine,
furniture, and clothing.
</P>
<P>
A total of 2.05 billion yuan of investment has been used for
construction and industrial infrastruction since its establishment
in 1989, according to official sources. 
</P>
</TEXT>
