<HEADLINE> Former Soviet Prime Minister Dies </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, June 1 (Xinhua) -- Former Soviet Prime Minister Nikolai
Tikhonov died of illnesses in Moscow on Sunday. He was 92.
</P>
<P>
Tikhonov, who served as the chairman of the Council of
Ministers of the former Soviet Union from 1980 to 1985, has been
in poor health due to a variety of diseases, the ITAR-TASS news
agency said.
</P>
<P>
Born in May 1905, Tikhonov was deputy prime minister and first
deputy prime minister from 1965 to 1976 before he became the prime
minister. He retired in 1985. 
</P>
