<HEADLINE> Albania Determined to Seek NATO Membership </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, June 1 (Xinhua) -- Albanian President Sali Berisha said
today that it is one of his country's unchangeable strategic
targets to enter NATO although the nation is faced with great
difficulties.
</P>
<P>
Berisha hailed the appeal by U.S. State Secretary Madeleine
Albright that NATO helps Albania rebuild its troops, a
presidential spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
At the NATO foreign ministers meeting last Thursday, Albright
said that the alliance should send a mission to Albania to assess
the conditions of the Albanian troops so as to facilitate the
rebuilding.
</P>
<P>
The situation in Albania remains volatile despite the
deployment of a multinational military force there. Rioting and
looting caused by the collapse of shady government investment
schemes in March turned into armed violence against President
Berisha in the south of Albania, killing more than 300 people.
</P>
</TEXT>
