<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Indonesian Pair Win Men's Doubles at Badminton Worlds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GLASGOW, Scotland, June 1 (Xinhua) -- Indonesia's Budiarto
Sigit and Candra Wijaya defeated Yap Kim Hock and Cheah Soon Kit
of Malaysia 8-15, 18-17, 15-7 to win the men's doubles crown at
the world badminton championships here on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Cheah and Yap were close to winning the first ever world
champion for Malaysia when they reached the match point at the
second game.
</P>
<P>
The Indonesians staged a comeback to tie the score 14-14 and
won the four-point setting 4-3.
</P>
<P>
The Indonesian duo, who beat Yap and Cheah in last year's US
Open, encountered little problem in the deciding game as their
opponents were apparently exhausted.
</P>
<P>
Yap and Cheah won the silver medal, while South Korea's Lee
Dong Soo and Yoo Yong Sung and Indonesia's Olympic champions Rexy
Mainaky and Ricky Subagja had the bronzes. 
</P>
</TEXT>
