<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, June 1 (Xinhua) -- Canada's Olympic gold medal sprinter
Donovan Bailey beat his U.S. rival, Michael Johnson, in a
one-to-one race in Toronto today.
</P>
<P>
Bailey was the first to finish the 150-meter track in 15
seconds, while U.S. sprinter Michael Johnson failed to reach the
end.
</P>
<P>
The race was supposedly to settle the debate over who is the
fastest man in the world. 
